  "name": "Variable Motor Speed",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Variable Motor Speed",
    "description": "Same idea as lesson 77 but a vibration motor on the drain branch: the pot divider sets NMOS gate voltage; USB → T → 150Ω → motor → drain, source → ground. A pot alone cannot spin the motor — the FET switches the current. Faster/slower feel is mostly stronger/weaker drive, not a precise RPM dial. Compare lesson 61 (tact → NPN → motor) and lesson 77 (pot → NMOS → buzzer). Pot at 270°; NMOS and motor at 90°."
  },
